resultRangeStart

public void resultRangeStart(long resultStart)
                      throws GnException
Set ordinal for the first result to be returned

Parameters:
resultStart - Set the starting position for the result

Remarks:

This option is useful for paging through results.

Note:

Gracenote Service limits the range size for some queries. If you specify a range size greater than the limit, the results are constrained. Additionally, neither Gracenote Service nor GNSDK returns an error about this behavior.

Important:

The number of results actually returned for a query may not equal the number of results initially requested. To accurately iterate through results, always check the range start, end, and total values and the responses Gracenote returns for the query (or queries). Ensure that you are incrementing by using the actual last range end value plus one (range_end+1), and not by simply using the initial requested value.
Throws:
GnException

queryNoCache

public void queryNoCache(boolean bNoCache)
                  throws GnException
Indicates whether a response is not automatically stored in the cache.

Parameters:
bNoCache - Set boolean to enable caching

Remarks:

Set this option to True to retrieve query data from a call to Gracenote Service; doing this ensures retrieving the most recent available data. Set this option to False to retrieve query data that already exists in the lookup cache. When no data exists in the cache, VideoID or Video Explore automatically calls Gracenote Service with the query request.
Throws:
GnException

resultFilter

public void resultFilter(GnVideoListElementFilterType listElementFilterType,
                         GnListElement listElement,
                         boolean bInclude)
                  throws GnException
Sets a filter for a Video Explore query handle, using a list value.

Parameters:
bInclude - [in] Set Boolean value to True to include filter key; set to False to exclude the filter
listElementFilterType - [in] One of the GnVideoListElementFilterType filter types
listElement - [in] A list element handle used to populate the filter value. The list element must be from a list that corresponds to the filter name.

Remarks:

Use this function with the GNSDK Manager Lists functionality to apply filters on and improve the relevance for specific Video Explore search results. Your application must have Video Explore licensing to use this function.

Note:

The system disregards filters when performing non-text related video queries, and filtering by list elements is restricted to performing a Works search using the following Filter Values:
  • kListElementFilterGenre
  • kListElementFilterProductionType
  • kListElementFilterSerialType
  • kListElementFilterOrigin
Throws:
GnException

resultFilter

public void resultFilter(GnVideoFilterType filterType,
                         java.lang.String filterValue)
                  throws GnException

Sets a filter for a VideoID or Video Explore query handle.

Parameters:
filterValue - [in] String value for corresponding data key
filterType - [in] One of the GnVideoFilterType filter types

Remarks:

Use this function to apply certain filters on and improve the relevance of Work text search query results.

Note:

The system disregards filters when performing non-text related video queries, and that filtering by
list elements is restricted to performing a Works search using the following Filter Values:
  • kFilterSeasonNumber text (integer as a string)
  • kFilterSeasonEpisodeNumber text (integer as a string)
  • kFilterSeriesEpisodeNumber text (integer as a string)

Throws:
GnException
